law.catch_line: License required to practice veterinary medicine -- No compensation for violator.
law.text: Except as provided in KRS 321.200, no person shall practice veterinary medicine or perform any of the duties usually performed by a veterinarian unless the person at the time holds a certificate of license to practice veterinary medicine issued and validly existing under the laws of this Commonwealth, as provided in this chapter. No person who violates any of the provisions of this section shall receive or accept any compensation for services rendered.
law.history: Amended 1992 Ky. Acts ch. 299, sec. 15, effective July 14, 1992. -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 181, sec. 15.
